17. Magn Reson Imaging Clin N Am. 2018 May;26(2):265-272. doi:10.1016/j.mric.2017.12.006.Use of Breast-Specific PET Scanners and Comparison with MR Imaging.Narayanan D(1), Berg WA(2).Author information: (1)SBIR Development Center, National Cancer Institute, 9609 Medical Center Drive,Rockville, MD 20850, USA. Electronic address: narayanand@mail.nih.gov.(2)Department of Radiology, University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine,Magee-Womens Hospital of UPMC, 300 Halket Street, Pittsburgh, PA 15213, USA.The goals of this article are to discuss the role of breast-specific PET imaging of women with breast cancer, compare the clinical performance of positronemission mammography (PEM) and MR imaging for current indications, and providerecommendations for when women should undergo PEM instead of breast MR imaging.Published by Elsevier Inc.DOI: 10.1016/j.mric.2017.12.006 PMCID: PMC5909988 [Available on 2019-05-01]PMID: 29622131 